in_m            = \n<!-- Population   ----------------------->\n|population_as_of                = \n|population_footnotes            =\n|population_note                 =\n|population_total                =\n|population_density_km2          =  <!--For automatic calculation, any density field may contain: auto -->\n|population_metro                =\n|population_density_metro_km2    =\n|population_urban                =\n|population_density_urban_km2    =\n|population_blank1_title         =\n|population_blank1               =\n|population_density_blank1_km2   =   \n<!-- General information  --------------->\n|timezone               = [[China Standard Time|China Standard]]\n|utc_offset             = +8\n|coordinates            = {{coord|44|36|N|117|37|E|type:adm3rd_region:CN-15_source:kolossus-dewiki|display=inline,title}}\n<!-- Area/postal codes & others -------->\n|postal_code_type       = Postal code <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... -->\n|postal_code            = \n|area_code              =\n|website                = \n|footnotes              =  \n}} \n'''West Ujimqin Banner''' ([[Mongolian language|Mongolian]]: {{MongolUnicode|\u182a\u1820\u1837\u1820\u182d\u1824\u1828}} {{MongolUnicode|\u1824\u1835\u1824\u182e\u1824\u1834\u1822\u1828}} {{MongolUnicode|\u182c\u1823\u1830\u1822\u182d\u1824}} ''Bara\u0263un Ujumu\u010din qosi\u0263u''; {{zh|s=\u897f\u4e4c\u73e0\u7a46\u6c81\u65d7 |t=\u897f\u70cf\u73e0\u7a46\u6c81\u65d7 |p=X\u012b W\u016bzh\u016bm\u00f9q\u00ecn Q\u00ed}}) is a [[Banners of Inner Mongolia|banner]] of [[Inner Mongolia]], People's Republic of China. It is under the administration of [[Xilin Gol]] League.\n\n==Climate==\nWest Ujimqin has a dry, monsoon-influenced [[humid continental climate]] ([[K\u00f6ppen climate classification|K\u00f6ppen]] ''Dwb''), with bitterly cold and very dry winters, very warm, somewhat humid summers, and strong winds, especially in spring. The monthly 24-hour average temperature ranges from {{convert|\u221218.7|\u00b0C|1}} in January to {{convert|20.2|\u00b0C|1}} in July, with the annual mean at {{convert|2.05|\u00b0C|1}}. The annual precipitation is {{convert|325|mm|in|abbr=on}}, with more than half of it falling in July and August alone. With monthly percent possible sunshine ranging from 57% in July to 72% in October and February, sunshine is abundant year-round, there are 2,882 hours of bright sunshine annually.\n\n{{Weather box\n|location = West Ujimqin Banner (1981\u22122010 normals)\n|metric first = Y\n|single line = Y\n|collapsed =\n|Jan high C = \u221212.7\n|Feb high C =  \u22127.8\n|Mar high C =   0.5\n|Apr high C =  11.8\n|May high C =  19.2\n|Jun high C =  24.2\n|Jul high C =  26.2\n|Aug high C =  25.1\n|Sep high C =  19.4\n|Oct high C =  10.5\n|Nov high C =  \u22121.3\n|Dec high C =  \u22129.9\n\n|Jan mean C = \u221218.7\n|Feb mean C = \u221214.9\n|Mar mean C =  \u22126.3\n|Apr mean C =   4.4\n|May mean C =  12.0\n|Jun mean C =  17.6\n|Jul mean C =  20.2\n|Aug mean C =  18.5\n|Sep mean C =  11.9\n|Oct mean C =   3.1\n|Nov mean C =  \u22127.7\n|Dec mean C = \u221215.5\n\n|Jan low C = \u221223.9\n|Feb low C = \u221220.9\n|Mar low C = \u221212.6\n|Apr low C =  \u22122.5\n|May low C =   4.3\n|Jun low C =  10.5\n|Jul low C =  14.3\n|Aug low C =  12.2\n|Sep low C =   5.1\n|Oct low C =  \u22123.1\n|Nov low C = -13.0\n|Dec low C = \u221220.5\n|precipitation colour = green\n|Jan precipitation mm =  2.6\n|Feb precipitation mm =  2.7\n|Mar precipitation mm =  6.5\n|Apr precipitation mm =  9.4\n|May precipitation mm = 30.4\n|Jun precipitation mm = 56.8\n|Jul precipitation mm = 93.6\n|Aug precipitation mm = 67.5\n|Sep precipitation mm = 31.9\n|Oct precipitation mm = 13.6\n|Nov precipitation mm =  6.4\n|Dec precipitation mm =  3.6\n|year precipitation mm=325.0\n|Jan humidity = 70\n|Feb humidity = 66\n|Mar humidity = 58\n|Apr humidity = 42\n|May humidity = 42\n|Jun humidity = 55\n|Jul humidity = 66\n|Aug humidity = 65\n|Sep humidity = 57\n|Oct humidity = 53\n|Nov hu